{
  "texts": [
    "We first note that the u(1) currents leave the (anti-)commutation relations of the psu(1, 1|2) 1 generators invariant, except for the anticommutator of the supercharges{S αAI m, S βBJ n } = -ϵ AB ϵ IJ c a (σ a) αβ J a m+n + ϵ αβ ϵ IJ (σ a) AB K a m+n + kmϵ αβ ϵ AB ϵ IJ δ m+n,0 + ϵ αβ ϵ AB δ I+J,0 Z m+n,where c a is a constant such that c -= -1 and c + = c 3 = +1 and conventions for the σ a can be found in [7].",
    "It is then clear that we need to impose Z n = 0 for all n. 5 This is why we treated the two scalings symmetrically in (2.3) and it ensures that the supercurrents (2.4) are each preserved under the scaling.The second U(1) current Y decouples from the theory because it is not generated by the commutators of the other generators.",
    "Instead, sectors with different Y 0 charge give different representations of the physics.",
    "It will play the role of a picture number: there is a copy of the full psu(1, 1|2) 1 theory at each eigenvalue of Y 0.",
    "We must take account of this in the construction of physical correlators [7,12,38], identifying two correlators that differ only in their Y 0 charge as physically equivalent."
  ]
}